    "created_at": "2026-05-06T20:15:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-06T20:15:03Z",
    "body": "I don't see the utility of this implementation. The idea of #1543 was to run each file through `clang-format` individually so that ninja can keep track of dirty files and efficiently format them. Compared to outsourcing the entire format operation to `git-clang-format` through a Python script, a commit hook would make more sense and is already set up through [`.pre-commit-config.yaml`](https://github.com/doldecomp/melee/blob/d97eb882de59110b888547a79ea4901286b7e1fd/.pre-commit-config.yaml). Maybe we should just document the [setup of pre-commit](https://pre-commit.com/#install) and add it to `requirements.in`.",
    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
